---
description: Use M-CANONICAL-DOCS format for public Rust docs (summary < 15 words, Examples, Errors, Panics, Safety, Abort sections as applicable)
alwaysApply: true
globs: ["**/*.rs"]
---

# Rust documentation

For public library items, use the canonical doc sections:

- Summary sentence (first line, < 15 words)
- Extended documentation
- `# Examples` when usage is non-obvious
- `# Errors` when the function returns `Result`
- `# Panics` when the function may panic
- `# Safety` when the item contains `unsafe` code
- `# Abort` when the function may abort
